# proxysh cursor rules

## Go
- Always use Go 1.25
- Always use ECDSA P-256 for certificate generation, never RSA
- Always use `x509.MarshalECPrivateKey` / `x509.ParseECPrivateKey` for ECDSA PEM encoding
- Use `github.com/spf13/cobra` for all CLI commands
- Use `gopkg.in/yaml.v3` for config parsing

## Proxy / TLS
- Never use `httputil.ReverseProxy` for WebSocket connections — always hijack and io.Copy raw TCP
- Always use `tls.Config.GetCertificate` for SNI-based routing
- Never bind to port 443 directly — always bind to 8443 and use pf redirect

## System
- Always use `sudo sh -c '...'` for /etc/hosts writes
- Always use `sudo security add-trusted-cert` for macOS CA installation
- Never skip `git init` before `gh repo create --source=.`
- Never set cert validity above 825 days (macOS limit)

## Static Site
- Never add a build step to docs/ — keep it as a single index.html file
- Always serve GitHub Pages from /docs on main branch
